title: Computer tomography scanner density by country 2017
summary: This bar chart has 29 columns on the x axis representing Country, and CT scanners per million population in each Country on the y axis.
The maximum CT scanners per million population 64.35 is found at Country Australia and the minimum is found at Mexico where CT scanners per million population is 6.12.
The highest Country Australia has 58.23 more CT scanners per million population than the lowest Country Mexico.
